	abstract = {Abstract
            
              Room‐temperature magnetoresistance effect is reported on a 2D molecular‐based magnetic system using only one magnetic electrode, unlike the typical spin‐valve systems with two magnetic electrodes. Charge transport is measured using a scanning tunneling microscope on a molecular monolayer of a Hofmann‐type network consisting of a 2D [Pt({CN})
