              , is the predominant order parameter in stabilizing helical structures. We further elucidate that the above itinerant spinless {ET} quadrupole induces a monopolelike orbital angular momentum texture in the momentum space, which can be observed via circular dichroism in soft x-ray photoemission spectroscopy measurement. Our findings highlight a critical role of the orbital angular momentum in chiral materials rather than less dominant spin angular momentum arising from the relativistic spin-orbit coupling.},
