              A chiral ligand, known as a symmetry-breaking reagent, can induce chirality in many achiral objects, including inorganic materials, for probing organic–inorganic interfaces, chiroptics, chirality induced spin-selectivity, and magneto-electrochemical phenomena. Chirality-induced paramagnetic heterostructures have not yet been explored in magneto-electrochemical and energy applications. Herein, we demonstrated the ability of
