	abstract = {Abstract
            
              The design of well‐defined assemblies of chiral molecules is a prerequisite for numerous applications, such as chirality‐induced spin selectivity ({CISS}). In this context, tripodal molecular films bear the advantage of better control of molecular orientation and alignment than analogous monopodal systems. To this end, we report on the synthesis and assembly property of
