	abstract = {Abstract
            
              The induction of chirality on pristine fullerenes through non‐covalent embedding in an asymmetric nano‐confinement has only been rarely reported. Bringing molecules with such a unique electronic structure and broad application range into a chiral environment is particularly appealing for the development of chiroptical materials, enantioselective photoredox catalysts and systems showing chirality‐induced spin selectivity ({CISS}). In this study, we report the formation of a chiral, configurationally stable Pd
              2
